# Sharpness (Added 2023 Aug 15)

[![image](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/19834515/260783035-12b7934f-3ff2-4dc5-86ca-d35937368d36.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..l1rAuZJA02DHKv4OdCJV6WkhxjRVqmrh2KZC5XPX-34)](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/19834515/260783035-12b7934f-3ff2-4dc5-86ca-d35937368d36.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..l1rAuZJA02DHKv4OdCJV6WkhxjRVqmrh2KZC5XPX-34)

Sampling sharpness is developed by Fooocus as a final solution to the problem that SDXL sometimes generates overly smooth images or images with plastic appearance.

Different from other parameters like Automatic1111â€™s cfg-scale, this sharpness never influences the global structure of images so that it is easy to control and will not mess things up (if you use same random seed). This option is relatively modest so that the image is not likely to be overcooked.

This option can solve 90% problems when the SDXL results are overly smooth.

**Example 1**

Prompt: a dragon  
Default setting. Random seed 12345

Sharpness = 2 (default):

[![image](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/19834515/260784333-3438067b-f3ec-46e3-b80d-6e453afeeedb.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..5hdwqD-GsI0yY8aj7KrmyvhHsVHz3vPgFylIklyU4l4)](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/19834515/260784333-3438067b-f3ec-46e3-b80d-6e453afeeedb.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..5hdwqD-GsI0yY8aj7KrmyvhHsVHz3vPgFylIklyU4l4)
